abstract: Riding two of the Internet’s big success stories, Google and YouTube, venture capitalist Michael Moritz of Sequoia Capital took the No. 1 spot on Forbes’s latest Midas List, an annual ranking of the top 100 dealmakers in technology and the life sciences.
lead_paragraph: Riding two of the Internet’s big success stories, Google and YouTube, venture capitalist Michael Moritz of Sequoia Capital took the No. 1 spot on Forbes’s latest Midas List, an annual ranking of the top 100 dealmakers in technology and the life sciences.

headline.main: Spinning Google and YouTube Into Gold

abstract: The sight of Larry Page and Sergey Brin is enough to strike fear into a newspaper editor’s heart. After all, the giant Internet company they founded, Google, has become a powerful force for democratizing the distribution of news, blogs and other forms of information, a trend that has left many in the industry bracing for the day when the print newspaper is dead.
